VENUES
======

POST /venues
------------
creates a venue

params:
	- service = string (eyeem, foursquare)
	- id = string (new venue id)
	- location[lat] = latitude
	- location[lng] = longitude
	- categories = string (foursquare category id)
todo:
	- lat/lng: standardize format for passing those params
	- categories not used if service=eyeem (which is now always the case!)
	- can we optimize this?
	- check for duplicates?
	- creation no longer allowed on foursquare - in this case the id provided must already be a valid venue on foursquare

GET /venues/search
------------------
params:
  	- lat = latitude (float)
  	- lng = longitude (float)
  	- cityName = string (current city [from device])
  	- cc = string (country code [from device])
  	- query = string (search string, min 3 characters)
  	- time  = string (All, Morning, Noon...) *deprecated from 2.2.0 onwards

notes:
	- Api Version 2.2.0 (needs client time of day)

todos:
	- endpoint should be only for native clients

POST /venues/foursquare
-----------------------
todos:
	- deprecated: remove from codebase for v3

GET /venues/foursquareToken
---------------------------
returns a user's foursquare access_token for EyeEm if available

notes:
	- requires authenticated user with native app access token